      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Verb: To Wake Up (فاق)",
          "arabic": "فعل: فاق (استيقظ)"
        },
        "text": "The verb 'فاق' (faq) means 'to wake up'. It's essential when describing your morning routine. Here's its present tense conjugation.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا كنفِيق",
            "english": "I wake up",
            "transliteration": "Ana kanfīq",
            "diacriticalNotes": "Note the kasra on 'ف' for 'kanfīq'"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "نتا كتفِيق",
            "english": "You (masc.) wake up",
            "transliteration": "Nta katfīq",
            "diacriticalNotes": "Note the kasra on 'ف' for 'katfīq'"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي كتفِيق",
            "english": "She wakes up",
            "transliteration": "Hiya katfīq",
            "diacriticalNotes": "Note the kasra on 'ف' for 'katfīq'"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هما كايفِيقو",
            "english": "They wake up",
            "transliteration": "Huma kayfīqo",
            "diacriticalNotes": "Note the kasra on 'ف' for 'kayfīqo'"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Verb: To Eat (كلا)",
          "arabic": "فعل: كلا (أكل)"
        },
        "text": "To talk about meals, you'll need the verb 'كلا' (kla) meaning 'to eat'. In Darija, it often conjugates with a 'yakol' stem.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أنا كناكل",
            "english": "I eat",
            "transliteration": "Ana kanakol"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "نتا كتاكل",
            "english": "You (masc.) eat",
            "transliteration": "Nta katakol"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هو كياكل",
            "english": "He eats",
            "transliteration": "Huwa kayakol"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "حنا كناكلو",
            "english": "We eat",
            "transliteration": "Hna kanaklu"
          }
